"Appellate Board" means the Appellate Board referred to in section 116;
(ab) "assignee" includes an assignee of the assignee and the legal representative of a
deceased assignee and references to the assignee of any person include references
to the assignee of the legal representative or assignee of that person;
(aba)
"Budapest Treaty" means the Budapest Treaty on the International Recognition of
the Deposit of Micro-organisms for the purposes of Patent Procedure done at
Budapest on 28th day of April, 1977, as amended and modified from time to
time;
(ac)
"capable of industrial application", in relation to an invention, means that the
invention is capable of being made or used in an industry;

"convention application" means an application for a patent made by
virtue of
section 135;

"district court" has the meaning assigned to that expression by
the Code of Civil
Procedure, 1908 (5 of 1908);

