that
the complete specification does not disclose or wrongly mentions the source or
geographical origin of biological material used for the invention;

that the patentee or the person under or through whom he claims, wrongfully
obtained the invention or any part thereof from him or from a person under or
through whom he claims;

that the scope of any claim of the complete specification is not sufficiently and
clearly defined or that any claim of the complete specification is not fairly based on
the matter disclosed in the specification;

that the invention so far as claimed in any claim of the complete specification was
secretly used in India, otherwise than as mentioned in sub-section (3), before the
priority date of the claim;

